<p>Side Man<ref class="image" href="/wiki/File:SideMan.jpg"></ref>Written by<ref target="/wiki/Warren_Leight" title="Warren Leight">Warren Leight</ref>CharactersJonesyTerryZiggyCliffordAlPatsyGeneDate premieredMarch 11, 1998Place premiered<ref class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/East_13th_Street_Theater" title="East 13th Street Theater">East 13th Street Theater</ref><ref target="/wiki/New_York_City" title="New York City">New York City</ref>Original language<ref target="/wiki/English_language" title="English language">English</ref>Subject Genre<ref target="/wiki/Drama" title="Drama">Drama</ref>SettingNew York City, 1953-1985</p>
<p>Side Man is a memory play by <ref target="/wiki/Warren_Leight" title="Warren Leight">Warren Leight</ref>. His inspiration was his father Donald, who worked as a <ref class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Sideman" title="Sideman">sideman</ref>, in <ref target="/wiki/Jazz" title="Jazz">jazz</ref> parlance a <ref target="/wiki/Musician" title="Musician">musician</ref> for hire who can blend in with the band or star as a solo performer, according to what is required by the gig.</p>

